ISS PEACEKEEPER: Coalition urban law enforcement

The Internal Security Specialists Peacekeeper is the Coalition's urban
law enforcement arm. They maintain order in CS cities, investigate
crime, root out D-Bee infiltration, and handle civilian security
matters the Army does not.

ISS Peacekeepers choose from Military, Espionage, Physical, and
Technical skill categories. They are trained in interrogation,
surveillance, arrest procedures, and crowd control. They carry
Coalition authority within CS territory and are feared by non-humans
and dissidents alike.

STARTING PACKAGE
  Attribute requirements: IQ 10, ME 10, MA 10.
  Equipment: ISS body armor, laser sidearm, restraints, personal
    communicator, CS identification credentials, and a field manual.

